# Project Name

<!-- This file teaches Claude Code about your project. Place it at your project root. -->

## Stack

<!-- List your tech stack -->
- Frontend: React / Next.js / Vue / Angular + TypeScript
- Backend: Django / FastAPI / Express / Rails
- Database: PostgreSQL / MySQL / MongoDB
- Cache: Redis / Memcached
- Background jobs: Celery / Bull / Sidekiq

## Commands

```bash
# Development
npm run dev              # Start frontend dev server
python manage.py runserver  # Start backend

# Quality checks (run before committing)
npx tsc --noEmit         # Type check
npm run lint             # Lint
ruff format .            # Format Python

# Testing
npm run test             # Frontend tests
pytest                   # Backend tests

# Database
python manage.py migrate # Apply migrations
```

## Architecture

<!-- Describe key architectural decisions -->
- Auth: Google OAuth → JWT → httpOnly cookies
- API: Frontend proxies all API calls through `/api/proxy/` (no direct backend calls from browser)
- Roles: Admin, Manager, Employee (defined in backend, checked on both sides)

## Key Directories

```
src/
├── app/           # Pages and routes
├── components/    # Reusable UI components
├── hooks/         # Custom React hooks
├── lib/           # Utilities, API client, helpers
└── types/         # TypeScript type definitions
```

## Conventions

- Use Tailwind utilities over custom CSS
- Use existing shared components before creating new ones
- API calls go through the centralized API client, not direct fetch
- Commit style: `type(scope): message` (fix, feat, refactor, perf, test, docs)

## Tool Preferences

<!-- Tell Claude Code which tools to prefer -->
- Use `qmd` for searching markdown docs (if indexed)
- Use `Grep`/`Glob` for searching code files directly
- Check `graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md` for architecture overview (if graph exists)
